{"id":"7109","name":"Get colorized pixel [JS1]","tagline":"A JavaScript one-liner to generate a 1×1 PNG of any color","icon":"ios12 c255 g59793","latest":"22099","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>A single line of JavaScript to get a base64-encoded pixel of any color you need (including transparency). This is a simplified version of my <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/6311/\">Unicolor PNG</a> shortcut. If you need more than a single pixel you can use that shortcut or just resize the output of this one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No error checking</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://editor.scpl.dev/?scpl=%40Icon%20brush%0A%40Color%20darkgray%0AComment%20%22A%20JavaScript%20one-liner%20to%20generate%20a%201%C3%971%20PNG%20of%20any%20color%20%E2%80%94%20%40atnbueno%20%282020-10-21%29%5Cn%5Cn-%20Examples%20of%20valid%20colors%3A%20red%2C%20%230F0%2C%20%23FF00FF%2C%20rgb%28255%2C%200%2C%20255%29%2C%20%23FF7F007F%2C%20rgba%28255%2C%20127%2C%200%2C%200.5%29%5Cn-%20No%20error%20checking%22%0AText%20rebeccapurple%20-%3E%20mv%3AText%0AURL%20%22data%3Atext%2Fhtml%2C%3Cscript%3Ewith%28document.createElement%28%27canvas%27%29%29%7Bwidth%3Dheight%3D1%3Bwith%28getContext%28%272d%27%29%29%7BfillStyle%3D%27%5C%28mv%3AText%29%27%3BfillRect%280%2C0%2C1%2C1%29%7Ddocument.write%28toDataURL%28%29.slice%2822%29%29%7D%3C%2Fscript%3E%22%0AGetFileofType%20%22com.apple.webarchive%22%0ABase64Encode%20mode%3DDecode%0ASetName%20name%3Dmv%3AText%0AQuickLook\">ScPL source</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\"><code>Canvas API</code> documentation at MDN</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The color can be any <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/CSS/color\">valid CSS color value</a>. Examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>red</li>\n<li>#0F0</li>\n<li>#FF00FF</li>\n<li>rgb(255, 0, 255)</li>\n<li>hsl(30, 100%, 50%);</li>\n<li>#FF7F007F</li>\n<li>rgba(255, 127, 0, 0.5)</li>\n<li>hsl(30, 100%, 50%, 0.6);</li>\n<li>transparent</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Don't download the shortcut</h4>\n<p>If you just want the code, there's no need to download the shortcut. Copy this and paste it in a \"URL\" action:</p>\n<pre><code>data:text/html,&lt;script&gt;with(document.createElement('canvas')){width=height=1;with(getContext('2d')){fillStyle='REPLACETHISWITHCOLORVARIABLE';fillRect(0,0,1,1)}document.write(toDataURL().slice(22))}&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Replace the <code>REPLACETHISWITHCOLORVARIABLE</code> fragment with the variable contaning the color, add a \"Get File of Type\" with type <code>com.apple.webarchive</code> below, and decode the base64 output to get the 1×1 colorized image.</p>\n<p>I use \"Get File of Type\" instead of \"Get Contents of Webpage\" to avoid that the user is misleading told that the shortcut uses Safari.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0 - Oct. 21, 2020, 4:53 p.m.</strong></p>"}